The President's statement acknowledges the 19th anniversary of the Rwandan genocide, expressing solidarity with the survivors and honoring the victims. It highlights the scale of the violence, with over 800,000 people killed, and acknowledges the ongoing pain and trauma experienced by those affected. The statement also emphasizes the importance of building a peaceful and prosperous future, committing to human rights, the rule of law, and the prevention of atrocities to ensure that such evil is never repeated.